# @SMJXV01P535F_BEG_WYUAU
VAR_STBXV18P316C VAR_TDSHV12P037A VAR_MZSHV08P263C VAR_KTHRV07P020A VAR_AAMZV02P066A حدثنا أبو بكر بن أبي شيبة قال حدثنا @TR1_YUAU@ يعلى @TR1_MUTK@ ومحمد ابنا عبيد الطنافسي قالا حدثنا محمد بن إسحاق عن @EW1_YAHA@ يزيد بن أبي حبيب عن أبي مرزوق قال سمعت فضالة بن عبيد الأنصاري يحدث أن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم خرج عليهم في يوم كان يصومه فدعا بإناء فشرب فقلنا يا رسول الله إن هذا يوم كنت تصومه قال أجل ولكني قئت. @SMJXV01P535F_END_WYUAU
PageV01P535
# @COMMENT: This is part of a series of traditions that appear to originate with Faḍālah b. ʿUbayd that discuss vomiting and its impact on the status of fasting. In this series there is a great deal of variation, but most suggest that Faḍālah was with the prophet and when someone offered him a drink or when he asked for a drink, Muḥammad was asked about the status of his fast. He replies generally that he was had been fasting but then vomited and was no longer fasting. In some traditions in the series there are comments about whether vomiting “breaks” the fast or if Muḥammad chose to end his fast after vomiting. There appears to be some dispute in the legal tradition about vomiting and its impact on the status of the fast, which these traditions address. The fragments are not separated into specific style types and are simply group by subject. They are witnessed by WHSDB: THSHV04P379A, THSMV02P096D, RZZIV03P063B, STBXV18P316B, TDSHV12P036D, MZSHV08P263C, KTHRV07P020A, AAMZV02P066A, and YNQXV11P036B; WYUAU: SMJXV01P535F, STBXV18P316C, TDSHV12P037A, MZSHV08P263C, KTHRV07P020A, and AAMZV02P066A; WMUTK: HBHXV39P361A, SMJXV01P535F, TDSHV12P037A, MZSHV08P263C, KTHRV07P020A, AAMZV02P066A, HJIIV05P180C; and WSACD: HBHXV39P385A, KTHRV07P019C, and HJIIV05P180C. This passage is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. It will be placed in the "*sunnah* section under *ṣawm*. @EC_01/07/24@

