# @SHBMV03P024L_BEG_WYUAU حدثنا أبو بكر قال ثنا @TR1_YUAU@ يعلى بن عبيد عن محمد بن إسحاق عن @EW1_THSA@ ثمامة قال خرجنا مع فضالة بن عبيد إلى أرض الروم قال وكان عاملا لمعاوية على الدرب فأصيب ابن عم لنا يقال له نافع فصلى عليه فضالة وقام على حضرته حتى واراه. @SHBMV03P024L_END_WYUAU
PageV03P024 235
# @COMMENT: This passage is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. Variations of this fragment are located in WYUAU: SHBMV03P024L; WAKMW: STBXV18P313C and BQSXV03P576E; WABAB: THSHV08P320A and SHBMV03P028G; WMUTK: HBHXV39P359B; and WSACD: HBHXV39P362A and KTHRV07P018B. It is a part of a series of traditions that originate from Faḍālah b. ʿUbayd, related to Ibn Isḥāq through Thumāmah b. Shufayy. According to BKHBV02P177D, Abū ʿAlī Thumāmah b. Shufayy al-Hamdānī only related from a few people, including Faḍālah, ʿUqbah b. ʿĀmir, and Qubayṣah b. Dhuʾayb. He appears to have been regarded as one of the people of Egypt. RZJXV02P466C states that Thumāmah related material to Ibn Isḥāq as well as Yazīd b. Abī Ḥabīb, the source of the only clarification tradition in the group found on in the WAKMW witness; all other the other traditions come to Ibn Isḥāq directly through Thumāmah. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān b. Aḥmad b. Yūnus al-Ṣadafī, in his history of Egypt, refers to him as Thumāmah b. Shufayy al-Hamdānī, as well as al-Uḥrūjī al-Miṣrī, although what “Uḥrūj” refers to in not known. al-Ṣadafī claims that Thumāmah participated in the raid on Rhodes (Rūdas) with Faḍālah b. ʿUbayd and that he died before 120/737 during the caliphate of Hishām b. ʿAbd al-Mālik (reign c. 724-743) (see TYNXV01P080A). al-Mizzī states that Thumāmah settled in Alexandria (MZTXV04P404A). The tradition witnessed by WYUAU and WMUTK (who were brothers and likely heard the story at the same time), state that the event took place in the time of Muʿāwiyah during the invasion of “Rūm” (see SHBMV03P024L and HBHXV39P359B respectively). WSACD also states in one of the traditions he witnessed that it occurred during the invasion of “Rūm” but does not place it in a time period (see HBHXV39P362A). According to Khalīfah b. Khayyāṭ, the invasion of Rhodes occurred in 59/678-679, the last year of Muʿāwīyah’s reign, under the leadership of Junādah b. Abī Umayyah (see SFTXV01P227B). There is, however, some dispute about the year that Faḍālah b. ʿUbayd died, some placing his death in 53, others in 67. Ibn Kathīr, quoting Ibn al-Jawzī, states that Faḍālah died in 55, apparently just before the capture of Rhodes, which he covers in the following section (see KTHBV08P078B). If this is accurate, the tradition may have had a foreshadowing element since it talks about death and burial just before Faḍālah’s own death. Placement should be in the year 55 or 56 under the heading of the Invasion of Rhodes. @EC_01/07/24@
